headline: 2 Consumer Stocks with Exciting Potential and 1 to Brush Off
summary: Consumer staples are considered safe havens in turbulent markets due to their inelastic demand profiles. Unfortunately, the sector hasn’t provided much protection lately as it pulled back by 10.4% over the past six months. This drop was disheartening since the S&P 500 held steady.
